    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I'm experimenting reducing the level of parallelism in the postgres tests.\r\nI'm finding that it's surprisingly easy for postgres to get OOM-killed when you run lots of tests at once. I think I saw the number of postgres processes peak at 137 or so (!)",
